<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2811] Infinite loop within RandomAccessBuffer </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2811</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve found an issue with RandomAccessBuffer which is triggered in a very specific corner case only:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the buffer has more than 1 chunk&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;read(byte[] b, int offset, int length) is used to read the data&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the data is read in portions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;one of the portions to be read is identical with the last remaining bytes of the current chunk&lt;br/&gt;
The current implementation won&apos;t advance to the next buffer, but reads the last bytes again and again.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
